Class UnknownIDException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • api.UnknownIDException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class UnknownIDException
extends Exception
    The UnknownIDException is thrown whenever a data set identifier does not address a data set. In other words, this exception occurs when no data set is found for the given identifier.
    Author:
    Loris
